<subSubSection id="C33365627D5DFFE6FF17EB54FE5EFB83" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="12" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9636E97D5DFFE4FF17EB54FD57FAE3" blockId="12.[151,1437,1436,2039]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FF17EB54FE90FD10" bold="true" box="[199,337,1544,1570]" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="5492884B7D5DFFE5FE8FEB54FE06FD10" box="[351,455,1544,1570]" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Holotype</typeStatus>
Male. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FDC3EB54FD2BFD10" box="[531,746,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">General coloration</emphasis>
. Entirely black to very dark brown, except mesonotum mostly orange, but blackened anteromedially. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FD81EB70FD4FFD74" box="[593,654,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Head</emphasis>
. Three ocelli on tubercle. Antenna dark brown with seven bead-like flagellomeres, apical flagellomere minute, nipple-like. Compound eye holoptic with minute sparse ommatrichia, divided into upper and lower section of larger and smaller facets by slight depression. Face not produced anteriorly. Clypeus rectangular, about twice as long as wide. Clypeus + proboscis short, subequal to length of antennae. Palps brown, five-segmented. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FE20EBE0FD80FDE4" box="[496,577,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Thorax</emphasis>
. Mesonotum with a subtle median and a pair of more distinctive dorsocentral grooves. Mesonotum largely bare with short dark sparse setae in median and dorsocentral grooves as well as laterally; much more numerous anteriorly. Katepisternum with patch of dorsal setae, anepimeron and metakatepisternum with a few setae. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FE11EA75FE3CFC70" box="[449,509,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Legs.</emphasis>
Slender, dark brown with dense short dark setae. Hind tibia nearly parallel-sided. Hind basitarsus long, slender, parallel-sided, approximately seven times as long as wide. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FBA5EA11FB6EFC54" box="[1141,1199,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Wing</emphasis>
. About 7.0 mm, light brown fumose, darker anteriorly. All veins brown, anterior veins bolder, pterostigma dark brown and darker than the membrane. R 
<subScript id="17AD34AC7D5DFFE5FE86EAFAFEB1FC86" attach="left" box="[342,368,1958,1972]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">2+3</subScript>
short, evenly curved, strongly divergent from R 
<subScript id="17AD34AC7D5DFFE5FC59EAFAFC62FC86" attach="left" box="[905,931,1958,1972]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">4+5</subScript>
, ending in C. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5DFFE5FB90EAC8FB70FC9C" box="[1088,1201,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Abdomen.</emphasis>
With short dark hair. Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5DFFE5FECEEAE4FE69FCE1" box="[286,424,1976,2003]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 24–26" captionStart-1="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId-0="13.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionStartId-1="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox-0="[171,1418,492,1907]" captionTargetBox-1="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId-0="figure-158@13.[168,1419,489,1909]" captionTargetId-1="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId-0="13" captionTargetPageId-1="14" captionText-0="FIGURES 24–26. P. schusteri sp. n., holotype male. 24. Habitus, scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 25. Male terminalia, ventral, scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm. 26. Male terminalia, dorsal, scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." captionText-1="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141099" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5141099/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="33">Figs. 25–30</figureCitation>
). Epandrium (tergite nine) rectangular, broader than long, nearly truncate posteriorly with a minute narrow median notch, though tergite is creased medially along entire length. Epandrium without posteromedian lobe or flap visible in dorsal view, but with a median keel on ventral surface visible in posterolateral view (
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5CFFE4FABFEDCBFF76FBE7" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Epandrial lobes apically rather truncate. Anterior margin of epandrium with slight broadly U-shaped excavation. Gonocoxites ventrally broader than long, with deep broad U-shaped posteromedian cleft; sclerotized median projection absent, but bottom of cleft broadly sloping into genital chamber and large membranous hump which can been seen in both posterior and ventral views. Lateral lobes of gonocoxites present, in ventral view inner (medial) surface sloping into genital chamber, in posterolateral view lobes broadly triangular though apically rounded. Gonostylus minute, in ventral view, pear-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5CFFE4FD5CEC33FD21FABB" box="[652,736,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–26" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[171,1418,492,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-158@13.[168,1419,489,1909]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 24–26. P. schusteri sp. n., holotype male. 24. Habitus, scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 25. Male terminalia, ventral, scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm. 26. Male terminalia, dorsal, scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141099" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141099/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), in posterior view rounded basally with a distinct thumb-like apical projection (
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5CFFE4FEB1ECCFFE75FA9F" box="[353,436,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
), and in posterolateral view rounded basally with a small thumb-like projection appearing much shorter than in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5CFFE4FDE5ECEBFD4BFAE3" box="[565,650,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
