<subSubSection id="C33365627D5EFFE6FF17EDE6FA98F9B7" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9636E97D5EFFE6FF17EDE6FA98F9B7" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FF17EDE6FE0EFBE7" bold="true" box="[199,463,186,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis &amp; Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FC90EDE7FBE3FBE7" authority="Hardy" authorityName="Hardy" box="[832,1058,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FC90EDE7FC15FBE6" box="[832,980,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
Hardy
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FB8CEDE7FAFDFBE7" authority="Fitzgerald" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="1998" box="[1116,1340,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FB8CEDE7FB01FBE6" box="[1116,1216,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. evansi</emphasis>
Fitzgerald
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished most easily by color differences: 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FD1CED83FCA1FBCA" box="[716,864,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FD1CED83FCA1FBCA" box="[716,864,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with thorax entirely orange (sometimes with some brown markings on thoracic pleurae), 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FD92EC5FFD64FA2E" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="1998" box="[578,677,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FD92EC5FFD64FA2E" box="[578,677,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. evansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with thorax entirely black, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FBD9EC5FFB48FA2F" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[1033,1161,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FBD9EC5FFB48FA2F" box="[1033,1161,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with scutum black anteriorly and orange posteriorly, scutellum orange, thoracic pleurae and postnotum black. The male terminalia of these three species are very similar; all have strongly reduced gonostyli, gonocoxites with ventral posteromedian margin deeply cleft, posteromedian margin of epandrium with only small cleft, and lateral lobe of gonocoxites present with medial (inner surface) sloping into the genital chamber. 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FCD2ECCFFCA4FA9E" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="1998" box="[770,869,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FCD2ECCFFCA4FA9E" box="[770,869,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. evansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very broad, shallow, V-shaped epandrial cleft (cleft about ¼ depth of sclerite) with a small median lobe, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FCBCECEBFC2CFAE3" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[876,1005,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FCBCECEBFC2CFAE3" box="[876,1005,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only a narrow notch posteromedially. The terminalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FE4AEC87FDEEFAC6" box="[410,559,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FE4AEC87FDEEFAC6" box="[410,559,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FDB7EC87FD29FAC7" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[615,744,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FDB7EC87FD29FAC7" box="[615,744,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ most in the shape of the gonostylus; in posterior view, the gonostylus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FEB3ECA3FE39F92A" box="[355,504,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FEB3ECA3FE39F92A" box="[355,504,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is triangular apically while there is a distinct thumb-like apical development in 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FA58ECA3FF3DF90F" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FA58ECA3FF3DF90F" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5EFFE6FEA1EF7FFDC9F90F" box="[369,520,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Figs. 29 &amp; 31</figureCitation>
) and in posterolateral view the apex of the gonostylus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FBADEF7FFACEF90E" box="[1149,1295,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FBADEF7FFACEF90E" box="[1149,1295,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very short and slightly hooked whereas that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FDE3EF1BFD75F953" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[563,692,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FDE3EF1BFD75F953" box="[563,692,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer and more digitate (compare 
<figureCitation id="13122A6C7D5EFFE6FBB6EF1BFAC7F953" box="[1126,1286,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Figs. 30 &amp; 32</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FACBEF1BFA5DF953" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[1307,1436,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FACBEF1BFA5DF953" box="[1307,1436,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6A7D5EFFE6FEEBEF37FE72F9B6" box="[315,435,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFB7D5EFFE6FEEBEF37FE72F9B6" box="[315,435,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-species-group (see Discussion) and will key to couplet 28 using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B187D5EFFE6FB5CEF37FAE5F9B7" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1164,1316,618,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref10022" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy’s 1945</bibRefCitation>
key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33365627D5EFFE6FF17EFD3FCFFF9C0" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9636E97D5EFFE6FF17EFD3FCFFF9C0" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">
